## 🔹 2025 (Ongoing)

### Multivariate Hurdle Count Models with Stratified MCCV

**Status:** Ongoing Research (PhD Dissertation Work)

### Objective
Develop and evaluate advanced multivariate count models for zero-inflated and zero-deflated data.

### Methods
- Developed a novel **Multivariate Generalized Poisson Hurdle Regression (MGPHR)** framework  
- Compared with Multivariate Poisson Regression (MPR), Multivariate Generalized Poisson Regression (MGPR), and Multivariate Poisson Hurdle Regression (MPHR)  
- Implemented **Stratified Monte Carlo Cross-Validation (MCCV)** for robust model evaluation  
- Designed stratified sampling based on joint outcome structure and tail behavior  
- Evaluated models using Negative Log-Likelihood (NLL), RMSE, and MAE  

### Results (Key Insights)
- MGPHR consistently outperformed competing models in predictive performance  
- Improved modeling of excess zeros and dependence across outcomes  
- Stratified MCCV provided more stable and reliable evaluation than standard random splitting  

### Tools
R (custom likelihood implementation, optimization, simulation)

### Contribution
- Proposed a new multivariate hurdle modeling framework  
- Developed custom estimation and validation procedures  

